## Expert 1
- I would first look at the weather conditions outside to determine how long it will take to dry the socks.
- Assuming the weather is good, I would estimate that it will take about 10 hours for each pair of socks to dry.
- Multiplying this by 10 pairs of socks, it would take 100 hours to dry all the socks.
- Therefore, it will take Tom 100 hours to dry seven pairs of socks..
